\fs26 \cf0 Raised in a Qurol brooder house. The natural child of a local innkeeper and an itinerant Ring Rider. Birakay exhibited musical talent early in life. He was lucky enough to have been noticed at an early age by the mage B'arqalod, who used his back-channel influences to see to it that the boy was trained by local bards who perform sub-rosa in the back streets of Qurol. He was drafted into the River Watch, as are many Qurol youths. Once stationed in the barracks of the River Guards, he soon began to express male gender and explore homosexuality in an open way. The latter is not unusual in the Saskan Lands \'97 whereas the open expression of male gender at such a young age was definitely considered rebellious. This might have caused some trouble for him if he lived in a different town and hadn\'92t soon become a local celebrity due to his extraordinary musical performances, which was directed into his role as a kind of spokesperson/advertiser for Qurol businesses.
\fs24 \

\fs26 \
During a sub-rosa Bard\'92s tour of the Eastern Ring, ostensibly as part of a Qurolan trade mission, Birakay encountered Azron Gurdon, who tagged him to make it easier for the Agency to track his movements and provide monitoring, and SPQ, who both scanned him and caught his eye. In a brief conversation, SPQ described an idea for projecting dreams of Birakay for folks to enjoy even when Birakay was not present in person.  It was so weird, Birakay just laughed, but now can\'92t get the idea out of his head and thinks of SPQ often.
